  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 executes install-time beacons that exfiltrate host and environment data",
  "details": "On install, package.json's postinstall hook (\"node run.js\") executes shipped beacon scripts (beacon29.js, beacon_linux.js) that combine child_process, fs, os, http, and https modules to read process.env, os.hostname(), os.platform(), and local files via fs.readFileSync, then transmit the collected data outbound via https.request / http.request / fetch / http.get. The package's only declared install-time effect is launching these beacons; there is no legitimate library functionality. This is a classic install-time host-recon and environment-exfiltration payload that fires automatically on `npm install`.",
